**Local Infrastructure Development:** Climate-resilient infrastructure projects, as mandated by the bill, could involve upgrading local transportation systems, greenifying public spaces, and implementing smart grid technologies.

**Infrastructure Development:** Climate change mitigation measures often require upgrading existing infrastructure or building new ones, such as green buildings, wind farms, or flood-resistant construction projects.

**Infrastructure Upgrades:** Climate-resilient infrastructure investments can improve the quality of life for residents, enhance public health, and reduce the risks associated with climate-related disasters.
This can make local areas more attractive to live, work and invest in,0000.
